1
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:13,889
Then Seong Wu and I should get ready first.

2
00:00:13,890 --> 00:00:14,890
That's right.

3
00:00:14,891 --> 00:00:15,949
Don't think about eating!

4
00:00:15,950 --> 00:00:17,089
(Don't think about eating jjajangmyeon!)

5
00:00:17,090 --> 00:00:18,090
We need to get ready.

6
00:00:18,790 --> 00:00:19,790
I need to eat.

7
00:00:20,690 --> 00:00:21,959
Wouldn't it be better to eat after the photo shoot?

8
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:23,459
Sodium might make you bloated.

9
00:00:23,460 --> 00:00:26,159
What will you do if sodium makes your face bloated?

10
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:28,969
If we wait, the noodles will get soggy.

11
00:00:28,970 --> 00:00:31,039
What's more important, eating or getting a nice photo shoot?

12
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:33,039
I don't know about that.

13
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:34,360
Fine. I'm leaving. Suit yourself.

14
00:00:34,570 --> 00:00:35,809
Let's go and see what happens.

15
00:00:35,810 --> 00:00:37,509
(Will Seong Wu be able to eat jjajangmyeon before the shoot?)

16
00:00:37,510 --> 00:00:38,510
(Meanwhile)

17
00:00:38,610 --> 00:00:40,109
Gosh, this is bad.

18
00:00:40,110 --> 00:00:41,680
Are those strawberries?

19
00:00:41,810 --> 00:00:43,810
(Ripe strawberries catch the winking cutie's eye.)

20
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:45,200
What are these strawberries for?

21
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:47,450
(Staring at the strawberries)

22
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:49,089
Strawberries are okay, right?

23
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:50,160
What do you mean?

24
00:00:50,460 --> 00:00:52,420
Strawberries are fruits.

25
00:00:53,020 --> 00:00:55,289
(Feeling disappointed, he removes the cover...)

26
00:00:55,290 --> 00:00:56,490
(and puts it back on.)

27
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:57,999
Don't eat anything!

28
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,000
(No!)

29
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,200
What?

30
00:01:00,201 --> 00:01:01,306
(No touching the strawberries)

31
00:01:01,330 --> 00:01:03,199
- Don't eat them. - Let me eat some strawberries.

32
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,970
Don't eat them! Why would you eat them?

33
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:08,810
(Is he watching out for his friend's bloating like Min Hyun?)

34
00:01:09,140 --> 00:01:11,280
He is so stern.

35
00:01:11,710 --> 00:01:12,909
He won't even let me eat strawberries!

36
00:01:12,910 --> 00:01:14,709
- Who? - Woo Jin.

37
00:01:14,710 --> 00:01:16,580
Why won't Woo Jin let you eat strawberries?

38
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:18,219
It's strange that he suddenly wants to eat strawberries.

39
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:19,450
It's strange and suspicious?

40
00:01:19,820 --> 00:01:21,989
- Why would he suddenly do that? - They're just strawberries!

41
00:01:21,990 --> 00:01:23,859
- You never know. - What?

42
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:25,460
Why would you suddenly eat strawberries?

43
00:01:25,890 --> 00:01:27,960
- Then you eat them first. - No.

44
00:01:28,430 --> 00:01:30,750
(Team Pink Sausage members are like a spear and a shield.)

45
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:33,176
(Shield Woo Jin sits next to Spear Ji Hoon and marks him.)

46
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,370
(He keeps his eyes on the strawberries as well.)

47
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,269
(His behavior is suspicious.)

48
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:38,840
(Looking around)

49
00:01:39,170 --> 00:01:41,740
(Why does the strawberry guard look so troubled?)

50
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:43,309
"Your mission is..."

51
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:46,810
"removing all seeds of one kingsberry strawberry."

52
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:48,779
(He needs to remove all the seeds using tweezers.)

53
00:01:48,780 --> 00:01:50,696
(It's a success if the strawberry becomes smooth.)

54
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:52,580
It's easy. Nothing is hard about it.

55
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:54,790
At most, it'll take 20 to 25 minutes.

56
00:01:54,850 --> 00:01:56,496
(Right after arriving at the mission location)

57
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:57,600
Are these the strawberries?

58
00:01:59,190 --> 00:02:00,790
(Checking the strawberries)

59
00:02:01,190 --> 00:02:03,560
(Wary of the surroundings)

60
00:02:03,830 --> 00:02:06,869
(He looks around and succeeds in obtaining the tweezers.)

61
00:02:06,870 --> 00:02:08,430
(However)

62
00:02:08,870 --> 00:02:09,870
(Bae Bae takes a peek.)

63
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:11,640
(Lovely Hwi lingers.)

64
00:02:11,870 --> 00:02:14,486
(Even the winking cutie makes it hard for him to take a strawberry.)

65
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:16,880
(When and how should I take a strawberry?)

66
00:02:20,980 --> 00:02:21,980
(Where are you going?)

67
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:24,179
(Cat Bae is looking for his prey.)

68
00:02:24,180 --> 00:02:26,780
(Chirpy birdie can't stop him.)

69
00:02:27,090 --> 00:02:29,820
(The winking cutie watches them.)

70
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:30,990
Don't eat them.

71
00:02:31,190 --> 00:02:32,659
- Don't eat them. - Why not?

72
00:02:32,660 --> 00:02:33,660
You never know.

73
00:02:34,290 --> 00:02:35,860
I want this potato dish.

74
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:40,430
(He tries to get Cat Bae to eat the potato side dish.)

75
00:02:41,070 --> 00:02:43,540
(Potato over strawberries)

76
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:46,270
The potato dish is tasty.

77
00:02:47,010 --> 00:02:49,140
(Eating potato)

78
00:02:49,470 --> 00:02:50,879
(With Cat Bae, he has a potato eating show.)

79
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:52,440
(Today as always, I'm the seeker)

80
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,079
(Sung Woon suddenly attempts to do his mission.)

81
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:55,109
(Singing Wanna One's song with a member in a relay)

82
00:02:55,110 --> 00:02:56,449
(What are you doing?)

83
00:02:56,450 --> 00:02:57,579
(Today as always, I'm the seeker)

84
00:02:57,580 --> 00:02:59,449
(Unresponsive)

85
00:02:59,450 --> 00:03:00,450
What are you guys eating?

86
00:03:00,451 --> 00:03:01,750
(This)

87
00:03:02,590 --> 00:03:04,460
Hey, how are those strawberries...

88
00:03:05,690 --> 00:03:07,250
Hey, how are those strawberries so big?

89
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:09,160
They're king-sized strawberries.

90
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,230
(Gulping nervously)

91
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:15,199
(Sung Woon picks one up right away.)

92
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:17,470
(He puts it in his mouth.)

93
00:03:17,570 --> 00:03:19,540
(His eyes shake.)

94
00:03:20,270 --> 00:03:22,769
(Perhaps my biggest mistake was failing to approach you.)

95
00:03:22,770 --> 00:03:25,640
(Had I been braver, I might've been able to have you.)

96
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,280
What should I do?

97
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:29,680
Don't eat anything.

98
00:03:29,681 --> 00:03:31,526
(I deserted Team Pink Sausage and a younger member for you.)

99
00:03:31,550 --> 00:03:32,550
Oh, my!

100
00:03:32,551 --> 00:03:33,889
(I can't believe I've lost you like this.)

101
00:03:33,890 --> 00:03:35,819
- Is it tasty? - It's the tastiest strawberry.

102
00:03:35,820 --> 00:03:37,396
- Why did you eat the strawberry? - Why?

103
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:39,359
(This strawberry beast continues to go after the strawberries.)

104
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,829
I want one too.

105
00:03:40,830 --> 00:03:42,559
- I want one too. - Try it.

106
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,200
- I want a strawberry. - Try it.

107
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:45,959
- These strawberries are the best. - Try it.

108
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,430
- The variety is seolhyang. - I see.

109
00:03:47,530 --> 00:03:49,270
(Not seolhyang, but the winking kingsberry)

110
00:03:49,370 --> 00:03:50,469
- Seolhyang? - Yes.

111
00:03:50,470 --> 00:03:52,316
- Why is it called that? - These strawberries are the best.

112
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:53,340
They're really tasty.

113
00:03:53,341 --> 00:03:55,886
(Will Woo Jin be able to succeed in his mission amidst the enemies?)

114
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:56,910
Hello.

115
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,339
(Please go that way for hair and makeup.)

116
00:03:58,340 --> 00:03:59,979
I'm looking for something.

117
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:00,980
What are you looking for?

118
00:04:00,981 --> 00:04:02,379
- What? - What are you looking for?

119
00:04:02,380 --> 00:04:04,649
It isn't here. Since it isn't here,

120
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:06,420
I'll go downstairs.

121
00:04:06,990 --> 00:04:08,089
It isn't here.

122
00:04:08,090 --> 00:04:10,390
(He looks here and there.)

123
00:04:10,890 --> 00:04:12,019
- I'm sorry, but... - Yes?

124
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:13,829
Is there a trumpet you've brought as a prop?

125
00:04:13,830 --> 00:04:15,530
(A trumpet?)

126
00:04:15,590 --> 00:04:17,229
"Your mission is..."

127
00:04:17,230 --> 00:04:20,529
"playing first verse of 'Arirang' on the trumpet..."

128
00:04:20,530 --> 00:04:21,890
"in front of at least one member."

129
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:23,299
I know how to hold it.

130
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:24,300
In the military band,

131
00:04:24,740 --> 00:04:26,670
I was an extra.

132
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,169
(The problem is that he has only held it.)

133
00:04:28,170 --> 00:04:29,910
I should've learned it in the military.

134
00:04:30,140 --> 00:04:31,640
I can't find it.

135
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:33,949
(Turning his head)

136
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:35,110
What? I found it.

137
00:04:35,710 --> 00:04:37,590
(The genius puppy gets a whiff of the trumpet.)

138
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,680
What are you guys eating?

139
00:04:38,681 --> 00:04:40,396
(How to save the trumpet, Step 1: Approach with a smile.)

140
00:04:40,420 --> 00:04:42,119
The strawberries look tasty.

141
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,120
Won't you eat one?

142
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:44,789
(Step 3: Take the trumpet and walk out as if it's yours.)

143
00:04:44,790 --> 00:04:46,119
(It was pretty natural.)

144
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,889
- Hey. - He is taking it.

145
00:04:47,890 --> 00:04:48,890
Shouldn't we catch him?

146
00:04:49,460 --> 00:04:50,629
(I understand, but let's eat strawberries first.)

147
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:51,859
Why is this strawberry square?

148
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:53,820
(Woo Jin continues to stare at the strawberries.)

149
00:04:55,030 --> 00:04:57,200
(Why is Woo Jin suddenly eating a strawberry?)

150
00:04:57,340 --> 00:04:59,639
I expected it to be sweeter.

151
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:00,709
The one I had was sweet.

152
00:05:00,710 --> 00:05:02,340
Big strawberries aren't that sweet.

153
00:05:02,470 --> 00:05:03,756
Big strawberries aren't that sweet.

154
00:05:03,780 --> 00:05:04,780
- Really? - Yes.

155
00:05:04,781 --> 00:05:06,210
(Trumpeting)

156
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,650
(At that moment, they hear an unfortunate sound.)

157
00:05:08,910 --> 00:05:10,649
(He succeeds in putting a strawberry in his sleeve.)

158
00:05:10,650 --> 00:05:12,349
(Checking the members)

159
00:05:12,350 --> 00:05:13,350
(He saves the strawberry in his pocket.)

160
00:05:13,351 --> 00:05:14,519
What time is it now?

161
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:15,889
It's 6:45pm.

162
00:05:15,890 --> 00:05:17,236
(At 6:45pm, Woo Jin obtains the tweezers and a strawberry.)

163
00:05:17,260 --> 00:05:19,860
(Meanwhile, Jjaeni opens the bag he has brought out unnaturally.)

164
00:05:20,020 --> 00:05:21,360
(A trumpet appears.)

165
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:23,430
(He tries the mouthpiece first for practice.)

166
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:26,230
(For beginners, it's hard to make sounds on a trumpet.)

167
00:05:26,630 --> 00:05:28,929
(I'll show you the skills of Kim Jae Hwan, the son of music.)

168
00:05:28,930 --> 00:05:30,869
(He succeeds in making a sound.)

169
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:32,640
(Blowing)

170
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:35,069
(The triumphant sound reaches the strawberry hunting ground.)

171
00:05:35,070 --> 00:05:36,539
- It's Jae Hwan. - He is doing his mission.

172
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:38,209
Jae Hwan, stop farting!

173
00:05:38,210 --> 00:05:39,210
It wasn't me!

174
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:41,380
(Wary)

175
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:44,650
I need to practice!

176
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,480
I'll get caught by a member.

177
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:49,150
"Is that a trumpet? I practiced how to play it."

178
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:50,490
It'll be like that.

179
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:52,559
Hey.

180
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,959
- What's up? - Are you busy?

181
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:56,589
You were the ace trumpeter in the military band.

182
00:05:56,590 --> 00:05:57,790
- Thank you. - Listen to this.

183
00:05:58,160 --> 00:05:59,260
(Farting sound)

184
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,570
(Farting sound)

185
00:06:00,770 --> 00:06:02,946
(Will he be able to cross over the Arirang Pass today?)

186
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:04,399
I can't do this.

187
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,400
Hold on.

188
00:06:05,401 --> 00:06:07,669
- Purse the upper and lower lips... - Okay.

189
00:06:07,670 --> 00:06:09,140
And make vibrations.

190
00:06:09,370 --> 00:06:10,779
(Trying again)

191
00:06:10,780 --> 00:06:13,639
- Even when I don't press anything, - Okay.

192
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:15,049
I keep getting high notes.

193
00:06:15,050 --> 00:06:16,930
- Is it following my vocals? - That's... Right.

194
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:19,479
Imagine hitting re.

195
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:20,849
(Hit the note as if you're singing.)

196
00:06:20,850 --> 00:06:22,889
(Thanks to his teacher, Genius Jjaeni improves in no time.)

197
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:24,210
- I'm hitting the notes. - Right?

198
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:26,219
To do that...

199
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:28,159
(The Korean melody can be heard faintly.)

200
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,160
That's it.

201
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:30,660
(Oh, yes!)

202
00:06:30,860 --> 00:06:33,099
(Jae Hwan's mission: Playing 1st verse of "Arirang" on a trumpet)

203
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:35,340
(Thanks to the best teacher, "Arirang" is coming along.)

204
00:06:35,570 --> 00:06:38,469
I need to take a break. I feel faint. I need to go inside.

205
00:06:38,470 --> 00:06:40,910
(While Jjaeni carries out the mission breathlessly)

206
00:06:40,970 --> 00:06:41,970
(Sighing)

207
00:06:41,971 --> 00:06:43,646
(Another member breathes out as much as Jae Hwan.)

208
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:45,579
(The winking cutie is anxious.)

209
00:06:45,580 --> 00:06:46,580
(Lifting)

210
00:06:46,581 --> 00:06:47,910
(The winking cutie is anxious.)

211
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,449
"Your mission is..."

212
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:53,549
"taking a solo selfie using all the members' phones."

213
00:06:53,550 --> 00:06:55,289
It isn't so bad. I think it's an easy mission.

214
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:56,419
I think I'll do it in no time.

215
00:06:56,420 --> 00:06:57,490
(However)

216
00:06:58,860 --> 00:07:00,559
(Spotting Jjaeni's puffer jacket)

217
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,690
(Looking around)

218
00:07:03,290 --> 00:07:04,730
(Don't look at me.)

219
00:07:05,630 --> 00:07:06,630
(Turning around)

220
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:08,769
(An actor with 16 million views sits down in a natural way.)

221
00:07:08,770 --> 00:07:11,770
(Rummaging)

222
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:13,869
- Am I doing this right? - It isn't here.

223
00:07:13,870 --> 00:07:14,940
(Jjaeni's phone is here.)

224
00:07:15,210 --> 00:07:17,240
(He scratches his head as he wanders.)

225
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:20,579
Shall I go to the makeup room?

226
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:22,179
While they're busy with their makeup,

227
00:07:22,180 --> 00:07:23,450
I'll carry out my mission.

228
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:25,649
(Meanwhile, the makeup room)

229
00:07:25,650 --> 00:07:26,919
(Is Jirung looking at his phone without doing the mission?)

230
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:29,189
"Have a conversation using 20 proverbs."

231
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:30,220
What's your mission?

232
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:31,819
- Me? - Yes.

233
00:07:31,820 --> 00:07:32,920
It's nothing.

234
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:34,760
What do you mean, it's nothing?

235
00:07:35,090 --> 00:07:36,090
(The naive target)

236
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:38,500
It's really suspicious that you're asking.

237
00:07:38,830 --> 00:07:40,630
- Why? - They say...

238
00:07:40,730 --> 00:07:42,799
that there is no smoke without fire.

239
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,569
Aren't you asking me to ruin my mission?

240
00:07:44,570 --> 00:07:45,900
(Please answer!)

241
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:48,969
Ji Sung, I told you earlier that we should help each other.

242
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:50,239
(He succeeds in using 4 proverbs.)

243
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,516
(There is no smoke without fire.)

244
00:07:51,540 --> 00:07:53,339
Hello.

245
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,480
(Ji Hoon enters.)

246
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:56,909
(Scanning the room quickly)

247
00:07:56,910 --> 00:07:57,980
Are you doing okay?

248
00:07:58,850 --> 00:07:59,919
I'm doing great.

249
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,519
Have you taken selfies using your phone?

250
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,520
Yes, I have.

251
00:08:03,490 --> 00:08:04,689
- Really? - Let's go with this.

252
00:08:04,690 --> 00:08:05,860
Okay.

253
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,689
(Retreating)

254
00:08:07,690 --> 00:08:08,960
This isn't easy.

255
00:08:09,730 --> 00:08:11,629
(Target number 2, Yoon Ji Sung, Phone location: In both hands)

256
00:08:11,630 --> 00:08:13,476
(He is using his phone at all times to study the proverbs.)

257
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:14,700
Ji Hoon.

258
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,569
You can't get the liver of a flea.

259
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:18,539
- What? - You can't get the liver of a flea.

260
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:20,240
Does a flea even have a liver?

261
00:08:21,140 --> 00:08:22,909
- Does a flea even have a liver? - Doesn't it have one?

262
00:08:22,910 --> 00:08:25,909
Seong Wu, they say we need to make hay while the sun shines.

